						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in front of the mosque.</p>						

						<p>Jayasimha (undated).</p>						

						<p>This inscription belongs to the reign of Jayasimha. The details of the date are not given. It records the gift of a piece of land made by the king to Mōchabbarasī as <hi rend="italic">kanyādāna,</hi> i.e. a gift. States that king Jayasiṁha was born in the lineage of Gautama, Śaradvat, Śantanu, Kṛipa and Śalya. The land granted is stated to be in the vicinity of Puttūr.</p>						

						<p>The record belongs to about 10th century A.D. The inscription is published (<hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.</hi> Vol. XXIX, p. 203).</p>						

						</summary>
